{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Auto Git Commit & Push",
  "description": "Automatically stages the saved file, generates a descriptive commit message based on the changes, commits, and pushes to GitHub",
  "version": "1",
  "when": {
    "type": "fileEdited",
    "patterns": [
      "**/*",
      "py,ts,tsx,js,jsx,json,md,txt,toml"
    ]
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "A file has been saved at {{filePath}}.\n\nPlease perform the following git operations:\n\n1. Wait for 10 seconds after a file have been saved\n2. Stage the file: `git add {{filePath}}`\n3. Analyze the file changes and create a clear, concise commit message that describes what was changed\n4. Commit with your generated message: `git commit -m \"<your message>\"`\n5. Push to GitHub: `git push`\n\nGenerate a commit message that:\n- Is clear and descriptive\n- Follows conventional commit format if appropriate (e.g., \"feat:\", \"fix:\", \"docs:\", \"refactor:\")\n- Summarizes the actual changes made to the file\n- Is concise (under 72 characters for the subject line)\n\nExecute all commands and report the results."
  }
}